<subSubSection id="C3776556ED1C3878FF78FD47FED4FD26" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1C3878FF78FD47FED4FD26" blockId="589.[136,779,173,1594]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FF78FD47FE9DFD62" bold="true" box="[189,344,649,675]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED1C3878FF78FD47FF3DFD62" box="[189,248,649,675]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED1C3878FEA8FD44FD71FD65" authority="(Stock, 1967)" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Stock" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[365,692,649,676]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Cyrtiidae" genus="Janius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spiriferida" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="brevis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FEA8FD44FDC2FD62" box="[365,519,649,675]" italics="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Janius brevis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED1C3878FDD9FD47FD6EFD65" author="Stock, J. H." box="[540,683,649,676]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock, 1967</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED1C3878FD04FD47FF7EFD07" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FD04FD47FF71FD04" bold="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(originally as 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED1C3878FE92FD65FD43FD07" authority="Stock" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1967" box="[343,646,683,710]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Prophioseides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FE92FD65FDFBFD04" box="[343,574,683,709]" italics="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Prophioseides brevis</emphasis>
Stock
</taxonomicName>
) by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED1C3878FF78FD21FE6FFC8C" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1C3878FF78FD21FE6FFC8C" blockId="589.[136,779,173,1594]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FF78FD21FEFBFCC8" bold="true" box="[189,318,751,777]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name honours the late Prof. Jan H. Stock who discovered the 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED1C3878FDC7FCDCFDF7FCED" box="[514,562,786,812]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">type</typeStatus>
species of the new genus. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED1C3878FF78FC9BFD81F9FB" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1C3878FF78FC9BFDE8FA4E" blockId="589.[136,779,173,1594]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FF78FC9BFEEFFCAE" bold="true" box="[189,298,853,879]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Remarks</emphasis>
. The mandible of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED1C3878FDDDFC9BFECBFC50" authority="Stock, 1967" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1967" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Prophioseides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FDDDFC9BFCCCFCAE" box="[536,777,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Prophioseides brevis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED1C3878FF4DFCB9FECBFC50" author="Stock, J. H." box="[136,270,887,913]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is very unusual for the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED1C3878FDA1FCB9FCC6FC50" authorityName="Chatton &amp; Brement" authorityYear="1911" box="[612,771,887,913]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Prophioseides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FDA1FCB9FCC6FC50" box="[612,771,887,913]" italics="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Prophioseides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because the exopod is reduced to a semicircular, unarmed swelling. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED1C3878FF3BFC75FE5DFC17" author="Stock, J. H." box="[254,408,955,982]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock (1967)</bibRefCitation>
described this species on the basis of a single specimen and did not determine whether the reduction of the mandibular exopod was a normal condition or a deformity resulting from injury or damage. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED1C3878FF38FB8DFE55FB9F" author="Stock, J. H." box="[253,400,1091,1118]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock (1967)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the left and right mandibles are of the same form, from which we infer that this is the normal structure of mandible for this species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED1C3878FF4DFB67FEE4FB05" author="Stock, J. H." box="[136,289,1193,1220]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 126" part="27" refId="ref331068" refString="Stock, J. H. (1967) Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Bulletin of the Sea Fisheries Research Station, Israel, 46 (Reports 27), 1 - 126." title="Report on the Notodelphyidae (Copepoda, Cyclopoida) of the Israel South Red Sea Expedition. Israel South Red Sea Expedition" type="journal article" year="1967">Stock (1967)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned other differences between 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED1C3878FD30FB64FF0EFB24" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1967" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Prophioseides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FD30FB64FF0EFB24" italics="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">P. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from its congeners: the body is shorter and thicker, the abdomen is inserted ventrally, the caudal rami are broadly elliptical, and the species is associated with the solitary ascidian 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED1C3878FE86FAFFFD51FA8A" authority="Savigny, 1816" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1816" box="[323,660,1329,1355]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Ascidiidae" genus="Phallusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FE86FAFFFE34FA8A" box="[323,497,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Phallusia nigra</emphasis>
Savigny, 
<quantity id="4C959B38ED1C3878FD99FAFFFD51FA8A" box="[604,660,1329,1355]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.61264" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" unit="in" value="1816.0">1816</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the Red Sea, in contrast to the association of all other congeneric species with the compound ascidians.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED1C3878FF78FA59FD81F9FB" blockId="589.[136,779,173,1594]" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED1C3878FF78FA59FE68FA70" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1967" box="[189,429,1431,1457]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Prophioseides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FF78FA59FE68FA70" box="[189,429,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Prophioseides brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be accommodated in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED1C3878FF4DFA77FEE2FA12" authorityName="Chatton &amp; Brement" authorityYear="1911" box="[136,295,1465,1491]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Prophioseides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="589" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED1C3878FF4DFA77FEE2FA12" box="[136,295,1465,1491]" italics="true" pageId="589" pageNumber="590">Prophioseides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without an unacceptable broadening of the generic diagnosis, and therefore a new genus, 
